Arduino
Platform for hardware projects

Hardware Hacking
Description
Arduino IDE and tools for programming microcontrollers used in hardware hacking, BadUSB attacks, and IoT testing.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which arduino
Install command:

sudo apt install arduino
Basic Syntax
arduino
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
arduino

Launch Arduino IDE	Program devices	
arduino-cli compile --fqbn arduino:avr:uno sketch

Compile sketch	Build firmware	
arduino-cli upload -p /dev/ttyUSB0 --fqbn arduino:avr:uno sketch

Upload to board	Flash firmware	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Install Arduino IDE
2
Connect Arduino board
3
Write or load sketch
4
Select board and port
5
Compile and upload
6
Test functionality
Understanding the Output
IDE shows compilation status and upload progress.

Important Warnings
•
BadUSB can be malicious
•
Respect device ownership
•
Use for authorized testing
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
